cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.HC 

This paper deals with the automated segmentation of white matter lesions in MR images of multiple sclerosis patients using machine learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning architectures, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The authors also mention the use of a prototype naive combination of the two methods, which could be related to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the methods in challenging conditions, which could be relevant to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
